@page "/"

<PageTitle>BlazorForm</PageTitle>

<div class="demo-intro">
    <h1>BlazorForm</h1>
    <p>A schema-driven form engine for Blazor. Define a form once — from a C# type or JSON Schema — and BlazorForm renders it, validates it, and manages its state.</p>
</div>

<div class="demo-card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">What's in the box</h2>
    <ul style="line-height:1.9; color:#334155">
        <li><strong>Schema from C# types</strong> — zero-config generation via reflection + DataAnnotations.</li>
        <li><strong>Schema from JSON Schema</strong> — import draft-07 documents; export any form back to JSON.</li>
        <li><strong>Fluent builder</strong> — type-safe, expression-based field configuration (React Hook Form + Zod ergonomics).</li>
        <li><strong>Validation</strong> — built-in rules, custom sync/async rules, and deep FluentValidation integration.</li>
        <li><strong>Conditional visibility</strong> — show, hide, or disable fields based on other values.</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-step wizards</strong> — per-step validation and conditional steps.</li>
        <li><strong>Array / repeater fields</strong> — add, remove and reorder nested items.</li>
        <li><strong>Pluggable renderers</strong> — dependency-free HTML by default; register your own widgets.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="color:#475569">Pick a demo from the sidebar to see each capability in action.</p>
</div>
